events.name: Initial meetup
events.description: We meet for the first time so this will be introduction of the first members. We will explain what GDG-s are and how we can  organize ours. The topics are not limited to only Google products so bring your curiosity with you and ask and discuss about any technology you know.

events.name: GDG Freilassing October Meetup
events.description:
Our October meetup is hosted by Abel KG. We are invited to use they're amazing location where we will have enough snacks and drinks to enjoy the presentations and activities.

Agenda:

• 18:00 Guests arrive

• 18:30 Welcome by Abel

• 18:45 Progressive Web Applications - Introduction

Progressive Web Apps are modern, mobile-first offline web apps that can compete with the best of those on native. They are meant to be the new standard of the mobile web.Progressive Web Apps combine the engagement of native apps with the reach of the web. They are a concrete part of the Web’s platform.Building a high-quality Progressive Web App has benefits, including making it easy to delight your users, grow engagement and increase conversions.

• 19:15 Break (15 min)

• 19:30 Server-less development with Firebase

Firebase is a Backend-as-a-Service — BaaS — that started as a YC11 startup and grew up into a next-generation app-development platform on Google Cloud Platform. Firebase frees developers to focus crafting fantastic user experiences. You don’t need to manage servers. You don’t need to write APIs. Firebase is your server, your API and your datastore, all written so generically that you can modify it to suit most needs. Yeah, you’ll occasionally need to use other bits of the Google Cloud for your advanced applications. Firebase can’t be everything to everybody. But it gets pretty close.

• 20:00 Break (15 min)

• 20:15 Live coding session

We are creating a Progressive Web Application using Firebase. Everyone can bring his Laptop and code together with us. We will use a prepared shell project so we can have a working application in 30 min. Further instructions for the preparation will be provided later. 

Guide for Live-coding preparation: https://goo.gl/Wez2dE 

• 20:45 Discussions and networking

We would like to thank Wirtschaftsjunioren Berchtesgadener Land for bringing us together with Abel KG.

events.name: Google Developer Group BGL December Meetup
events.description:
Amazing time with the Google Developer Group BGL

Our December meetup is hosted by Talsen Team GmbH (http://talsen.team/index.html). We are invited to use they're amazing location where we will have enough snacks and drinks to enjoy the presentations and activities.

Agenda:

• 18:00 Guests arrive

• 18:30 Welcome by Tarik (organiser) and Hans (Talsen Team)

• 18:45 Agile Software Development – Ideas, Values, Methods and Tools by Dr.-Ing. Hans Egermeier

The presentation is about agile software development. Starting with the basic motivation and the benefits of agile software development the presentation also covers topics like the agile manifesto, requirement techniques, basic process building blocks and necessary tool support. The topics are presented in a practical way and explained with case studies from real development teams • 19:15 Break (15 min)

• 19:30 Docker by David Lechner

Docker is a software technology providing containers, promoted by the company Docker, Inc. Docker provides an additional layer of abstraction and automation of operating-system-level virtualization on Windows and Linux. Docker uses the resource isolation features of the Linux kernel such as cgroups and kernel namespaces, and a union-capable file system such as OverlayFS and others to allow independent "containers" to run within a single Linux instance, avoiding the overhead of starting and maintaining virtual machines (VMs).

• 20:00 Break (15 min)

• 20:15 Live coding session with Tarik

We will again create a new and fresh Progressive Web Application and now also create new components in it that we can use at the end of the session.

Guide for Live-coding: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HIaIMw6HQw8EXId6fhW_Ei8ttpl_wM3o9ExnJu5XX1I/edit?usp=sharing

• 20:45 Discussions and networking

events.name: Google Developer Group BGL UX Meetup
events.description:
• Was wir unternehmen werden
Amazing time with the Google Developer Group BGL

Our UX meetup is hosted by #Urgestain (http://urgestain.de). We are invited to use they're amazing location that is equipped with a film studio and other cool stuff. Check it out in this video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WaqI8qAxzJ8

Our agenda:

• 18:00 Guests arrive

• 18:30 Welcome by Tarik (organiser) and Marc Cheret (#Urgestain)

• 18:45 UX beyond UI - A user centered design approach for game changing products. – by Florian Heuse

User experience design is more than UI. UX or User Experience encompasses every aspect oft the end-user’s interaction with a product, service, or company. It’s obvious that you want to meet the exact needs of your customer and to reduce development costs by being more efficient. UX design as a discipline combines traditional Human Computer Interaction methods with lean practices. As a kickoff this talk will give you a brief overview of the concepts of Usability, User Experience and UI. Afterwards you will learn about a structured design process called User Experience Engineering Lifecycle. It’s all about enhancing user satisfaction with your product by improving the usability, accessibility, and pleasure provided in the interaction with it. At the end oft the talk you will understand that UI is only one part of a bigger dimension and you will be able to boost your performance in engineering your next minimum viable product. Make your customers fall in love with your products. Are you ready for the challenge?

• 19:30 Playing with Google Daydream devices

We as Google Developer Group received two Google Daydream VR devices as present. We will check them out. More about theme here https://store.google.com/product/google_daydream_view?utm_source=en-ha-na-sem&utm_campaign=daydream&utm_medium=text&utm_term=pid_209138112-cid_0-aid_408818616&utm_content=bkws&gclid=CjwKCAiAn5rUBRA3EiwAUCWb29X_NJ1EUZudksLXdSc3_BCBAChp55WGNGAlzI5dChB-2-cl2HEM_BoCYqEQAvD_BwE&dclid=CK3ZtraMq9kCFc2LUQodM5sP1w

• 20:00 Talks, fun , discussions and networking

On our last event we spend a lot of time with the presentations so had less time for our talks. Now we will make it the other way and concentrate more on discussions and experience exchange. We will also discuss our future meetups. Google has amazing study jams we could participate.

• Was sollst du mitbringen

• Wichtig zu wissen

events.name: DACHFest 2018 (DevFest DACH)
events.description:
For this year's DevFest season, GDG and WTM communities of Germany, Austria, and Switzerland are all working together to organize our largest event yet: DACHFest!

DACHFest is a two-day DevFest conference focused on making a difference. Meet technology experts, discover all the different ways in which emerging technology is transforming lives, find out how to make your apps and websites friendly towards everyone, learn the secrets of building and nurturing a diverse community — let our speakers surprise and inspire you! And don't forget to make new friends: there will be plenty of opportunities to meet people passionate about your favorite things. ❤️

Join us in Munich on November 10–11 for two days full of talks, workshops, showcases, networking, and fun!

DACHFest is a paid event, but diversity scholarships are available for people who belong to underrepresented groups in tech or cannot afford a ticket.

Website: https://dachfest.com
Twitter: https://twitter.com/dachfest
Call for papers (until September 15): http://papercall.io/dachfest18

events.description:
Let's review the Google I/O together trough recorded Sessions you are interested in or the Keynote and talk about the stuff we like or don't like.

Ask questions how it is to go to the Google I/O.

What is this Google I/O?
What is new and when could we see it in germany?
Why is Tarik coming back from Google I/O if he could hide somewhere there and wait for the next year?

Answers to those and other questions you will fin at our next meetup!

If you don't know what the Google I/O you should definitely come to our meetup :)

And of course I'm coming with SWAAAAGGG :)
